      {
        "id": "047d5febacaf2cf3443b293f20b65124eed8bb64",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1071,
          "name": "Michael Hwang",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "mhwang@research.att.com",
          "username": "researchmike"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-18 02:39:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> docker-login is only needed when doing docker pull or push\n > commands.\n > These jobs are just doing maven goals.\n > \n > I am happy to look into any failure on any of these jobs if you\n > have one.\n\nHi Jessica\n\nI have a couple projects that make use of Spotify's Docker Maven plugin and have the `deploy` maven goal to do a Docker push.  Thus the need for `docker-login`.  Here's an example of a job that's failing:\n\nhttps://jenkins.onap.org/job/dcaegen2-platform-inventory-api-master-merge-java/5/console\n\nNote the authentication error way down below.  My thought is that there shouldn't be any harm performing the `docker-login` even when not used.\n\nThanks\n\nMike",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
